WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:03.650
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:03.650 --> 00:00:07.820
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates, obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.660
What he said in his final moments drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:11.660 --> 00:00:13.660
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:13.660 --> 00:00:15.450
Go ahead.

7
00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:16.660
Find it!

8
00:00:16.660 --> 00:00:19.250
Everything is right where I left it!

9
00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:26.380
People set their sights on the Grand Line in pursuit of their dreams.

10
00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:29.630
The world has truly entered the Great Pirate Era!

11
00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:35.640
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

12
00:00:30.470 --> 00:00:35.640
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

13
00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:41.440
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

14
00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:42.690
One Piece!
ONE PIECE

15
00:00:47.900 --> 00:00:52.700
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind
Rashinban nante juutai no moto

16
00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:58.500
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide
Netsu ni ukasare kaji wo toru no sa

17
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:04.540
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals
Hokori kabutteta takara no chizu mo

18
00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:09.760
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real
Tashikameta no nara densetsu janai!

19
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.710
When the world's got you down,

20
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:16.850
Kojin teki na arashi wa dare ka no

21
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.850
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

22
00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:22.190
Their biorhythm will carry you through
BIORHYTHM nokkatte

23
00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.230
We're gonna make the most of it
Omoi sugoseba ii!

24
00:01:26.110 --> 00:01:31.400
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

25
00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:36.990
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

26
00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.040
Got some change to my name,
POCKET no COIN

27
00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.250
and maybe you wanna be my friend?
Soreto YOU WANNA BE MY FRIEND?

28
00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:48.130
We are, we are on the cruise!
WE ARE, WE ARE ON THE CRUISE!

29
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:49.760
WE ARE!

30
00:01:52.880 --> 00:01:54.050
Gin!

31
00:01:54.510 --> 00:01:58.970
No matter how incredible he was
in the past, he's just a cook now.

32
00:01:59.310 --> 00:02:01.730
Blowing his brains out would be easy.

33
00:02:02.940 --> 00:02:05.900
You want to save
this man, right, Sanji?

34
00:02:05.900 --> 00:02:09.400
Then please... leave this ship
without a fight.

35
00:02:09.860 --> 00:02:12.740
I don't want to kill you.

36
00:02:15.530 --> 00:02:16.910
Leave this ship?

37
00:02:17.780 --> 00:02:19.290
Piss off!

38
00:02:21.040 --> 00:02:24.540
You look ridiculous, you old fart.

39
00:02:24.540 --> 00:02:27.880
What kind of example are you
setting for the fighting cooks?

40
00:02:28.630 --> 00:02:31.710
I don't need a lecture
from a little eggplant.

41
00:02:31.710 --> 00:02:34.090
Who are you calling
"little eggplant," old fart?!

42
00:02:34.090 --> 00:02:36.430
Quit treating me like a kid already!

43
00:02:36.430 --> 00:02:38.050
Sanji, you son of a...

44
00:02:38.050 --> 00:02:40.600
He's not turning his back
on the head chef, is he?

45
00:02:40.600 --> 00:02:42.020
Gin!

46
00:02:42.020 --> 00:02:44.310
Point that gun at me instead.

47
00:02:45.190 --> 00:02:47.440
Are you stupid?! You're gonna die!

48
00:02:47.440 --> 00:02:48.400
I might.

49
00:02:49.020 --> 00:02:51.650
Sanji, why...?

50
00:02:51.650 --> 00:02:57.280
If you're that desperate to die,
I will give you a gentleman's death.

51
00:02:58.370 --> 00:03:03.000
But you'll need to hold still, or else
we'll blow the proprietor's head off.

52
00:03:04.710 --> 00:03:06.920
Pristine Pearl...

53
00:03:06.920 --> 00:03:08.130
Present!

54
00:03:10.130 --> 00:03:11.130
Sanji!

55
00:03:11.550 --> 00:03:13.510
Why didn't you dodge that?!

56
00:03:14.260 --> 00:03:18.800
If I did, that damn lackey
would pull the trigger.

57
00:03:19.430 --> 00:03:20.680
Why?

58
00:03:20.680 --> 00:03:23.430
If you leave this restaurant,
then everyone lives!

59
00:03:23.430 --> 00:03:24.640
It's a no-brainer!

60
00:03:24.640 --> 00:03:26.810
This restaurant is his treasure!

61
00:03:30.610 --> 00:03:34.780
It's my fault the old fart
lost everything...

62
00:03:37.520 --> 00:03:38.990
His power...

63
00:03:41.200 --> 00:03:42.700
His dream...

64
00:03:45.200 --> 00:03:46.750
So I've decided...

65
00:03:47.120 --> 00:03:50.290
I won't let that old fart
lose anything else!

66
00:03:51.340 --> 00:03:52.460
Sanji! Watch out!

67
00:03:52.460 --> 00:03:54.010
Pearl...

68
00:03:54.090 --> 00:03:55.550
Close!

69
00:03:55.550 --> 00:03:57.130
Sanji!

70
00:04:02.350 --> 00:04:03.850
The All Blue?

71
00:04:03.850 --> 00:04:04.720
Yeah!

72
00:04:04.720 --> 00:04:06.390
It's a legendary sea.

73
00:04:06.390 --> 00:04:09.100
It's definitely out there somewhere!

74
00:04:08.980 --> 00:04:15.740
Because of a Dream

75
00:04:15.740 --> 00:04:17.740
Don't be silly!

76
00:04:15.780 --> 00:04:21.660
The Orbit
A Passenger Ship

77
00:04:17.740 --> 00:04:20.530
I mean, there is a legend like that...

78
00:04:20.530 --> 00:04:23.990
We're seafaring cooks, after all,

79
00:04:23.990 --> 00:04:26.620
so we've all dreamed
of that sea at one point.

80
00:04:26.620 --> 00:04:27.620
Right?

81
00:04:26.660 --> 00:04:31.080
Sanji (9 Years Ago)
Cook's Apprentice
Passenger Ship

82
00:04:27.620 --> 00:04:31.080
I'll definitely find that sea someday!

83
00:04:31.080 --> 00:04:33.460
You say you'll find it, but...

84
00:04:33.460 --> 00:04:37.340
For starters, do you even know
what kind of place the All Blue is?

85
00:04:37.340 --> 00:04:39.470
Of course I do! I'm not an idiot!

86
00:04:40.050 --> 00:04:43.970
The East Blue, West Blue,
North Blue, and South Blue...

87
00:04:43.970 --> 00:04:48.100
A sea where fish
from all four seas live...

88
00:04:48.100 --> 00:04:50.140
That's the All Blue.

89
00:04:50.140 --> 00:04:53.400
To seafaring cooks,
it's an irresistible paradise!

90
00:04:55.690 --> 00:04:56.940
That's my dream!

91
00:04:57.190 --> 00:04:58.820
That's the place!

92
00:04:58.820 --> 00:05:02.070
The seafood in those waters
is from all over the world.

93
00:05:02.070 --> 00:05:04.830
Any cook would be itching
to show their skills there!

94
00:05:04.830 --> 00:05:05.660
Yeah.

95
00:05:05.990 --> 00:05:09.080
It's worth risking your life
to look for that sea.

96
00:05:09.080 --> 00:05:10.670
That is, if such a sea exists...

97
00:05:10.670 --> 00:05:11.330
What?

98
00:05:11.670 --> 00:05:15.170
There's no way a miracle sea
like the All Blue could exist.

99
00:05:15.170 --> 00:05:17.340
It's obvious when you think about it.

100
00:05:17.960 --> 00:05:21.930
Some daydreaming cook
must have told it as a tall tale.

101
00:05:21.930 --> 00:05:24.260
Now, enough with the silly stories.

102
00:05:24.260 --> 00:05:26.140
Go bus the tables, Sanji.

103
00:05:31.060 --> 00:05:34.020
What a waste to leave
so much food...

104
00:05:34.020 --> 00:05:36.320
They barely touched this one.

105
00:05:36.320 --> 00:05:37.900
I was sure they'd like it.

106
00:05:37.900 --> 00:05:40.820
Customers these days
sure are spoiled.

107
00:05:40.820 --> 00:05:43.660
You need to stop eating
the customers' leftovers.

108
00:05:43.660 --> 00:05:46.240
Some of the food I threw out
earlier looked gross.

109
00:05:46.240 --> 00:05:50.040
You're still only half a cook
if you say things like that.

110
00:05:50.040 --> 00:05:53.370
Don't forget we're seafaring cooks.

111
00:05:53.370 --> 00:05:58.800
The sea is an unpredictable place,
so it's best not to waste food.

112
00:05:59.170 --> 00:06:01.380
Why don't you have some, too, huh?

113
00:06:01.380 --> 00:06:03.130
I don't want it!

114
00:06:04.720 --> 00:06:08.180
Everyone, calm down!
Please calm down!

115
00:06:12.390 --> 00:06:13.230
Pirates!

116
00:06:15.270 --> 00:06:16.480
Pirates?!

117
00:06:20.740 --> 00:06:22.530
That ship belongs to...

118
00:06:22.530 --> 00:06:24.360
the Cook Pirates!

119
00:06:24.360 --> 00:06:26.240
It's Red Leg Zeff!

120
00:06:27.160 --> 00:06:30.290
Looks like they came back
from the Grand Line!

121
00:06:38.250 --> 00:06:40.920
"Red Leg" Zeff
Cook Pirates

122
00:06:42.470 --> 00:06:46.340
You're the pirate captain
Red Leg Zeff I presume?

123
00:06:46.340 --> 00:06:47.720
How may I assist you?

124
00:06:48.140 --> 00:06:49.140
Plunder!

125
00:06:50.720 --> 00:06:54.350
Steal all their valuables!

126
00:06:57.270 --> 00:06:58.560
Dammit...

127
00:06:58.560 --> 00:07:01.400
Dammit! I can't die here...

128
00:07:01.400 --> 00:07:03.950
These scumbags can't kill me!

129
00:07:05.150 --> 00:07:06.450
Whoa!

130
00:07:06.450 --> 00:07:07.780
What's with this brat?

131
00:07:08.280 --> 00:07:12.410
Hey, punk. It's dangerous
to swing something like that around.

132
00:07:12.410 --> 00:07:15.000
Look. Blood. I'm so injured.

133
00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:18.750
Shut up! I'm not gonna be
killed by bastards like you!

134
00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:20.750
Sanji!

135
00:07:20.750 --> 00:07:23.210
Stop it! Don't fight back!

136
00:07:24.300 --> 00:07:28.180
That kid's asking for it!
Just hurry up and kill him!

137
00:07:28.180 --> 00:07:29.180
I don't want to die!

138
00:07:29.180 --> 00:07:32.680
If I am gonna die, I'd like to take
a few of you bastards out first!

139
00:07:36.730 --> 00:07:37.440
Sanji!

140
00:07:38.600 --> 00:07:41.690
Man, you did it, Captain.

141
00:07:40.150 --> 00:07:41.690
Always so merciless.

142
00:07:52.200 --> 00:07:54.160
I'm not gonna die...!

143
00:07:56.580 --> 00:07:57.540
I...

144
00:07:58.790 --> 00:08:03.050
Someday... I will find the All Blue!

145
00:08:06.510 --> 00:08:08.840
He said "All Blue"!

146
00:08:08.840 --> 00:08:11.850
That's one hell of a goal!

147
00:08:11.850 --> 00:08:17.480
Captain, tell him how we couldn't
even find it in the Grand Line.

148
00:08:18.060 --> 00:08:20.440
That idiot! He's still
spouting that nonsense...

149
00:08:26.940 --> 00:08:31.570
I'm not gonna be killed by some
damn pirates in a place like this!

150
00:08:32.280 --> 00:08:34.450
Captain! Let's withdraw!

151
00:08:34.450 --> 00:08:38.080
This storm is taking
a turn for the worse!

152
00:08:38.460 --> 00:08:40.040
That decides it, men!

153
00:08:40.040 --> 00:08:42.670
Hurry and load
the treasure onto our ship!

154
00:08:42.670 --> 00:08:43.960
We're withdrawing!

155
00:08:58.810 --> 00:08:59.480
Sanji!

156
00:09:00.600 --> 00:09:02.190
Captain!

157
00:09:08.990 --> 00:09:10.320
That damn kid!

158
00:09:14.280 --> 00:09:15.530
Captain!

159
00:09:15.990 --> 00:09:18.620
Why'd he do that just for a little brat?!

160
00:10:00.410 --> 00:10:02.750
Finally awake, little eggplant?

161
00:10:02.750 --> 00:10:04.960
You're quite lucky.

162
00:10:05.290 --> 00:10:06.130
Pirat–

163
00:10:08.090 --> 00:10:10.010
Figures you can't move.

164
00:10:10.010 --> 00:10:13.050
You think you can just
shrug off a kick from me?

165
00:10:13.590 --> 00:10:14.890
So the ships...?

166
00:10:14.890 --> 00:10:17.600
Who knows? The sea was very rough.

167
00:10:17.600 --> 00:10:20.140
It's likely they were
completely destroyed.

168
00:10:20.520 --> 00:10:23.940
We're the only ones
who washed up here...

169
00:10:23.940 --> 00:10:27.610
This rocky mound has
neither fruits nor animals.

170
00:10:28.320 --> 00:10:30.940
Sure, there are fish in the sea below,

171
00:10:30.940 --> 00:10:34.070
but the waves have
curved the rock inwards,

172
00:10:34.450 --> 00:10:37.410
which sadly means going down
is a one-way trip.

173
00:10:38.580 --> 00:10:40.830
All of this is your fault!

174
00:10:40.830 --> 00:10:42.290
I'll kill you!

175
00:10:42.290 --> 00:10:43.540
Complain all you like.

176
00:10:43.540 --> 00:10:45.790
We have no choice
but to wait for help.

177
00:10:45.790 --> 00:10:48.960
But if no one comes, we'll just
dry up and become skeletons.

178
00:10:48.960 --> 00:10:50.460
I'll become...

179
00:10:50.960 --> 00:10:51.960
a skeleton?

180
00:10:52.550 --> 00:10:55.840
That bag over there is your share.

181
00:10:55.840 --> 00:10:56.590
What?

182
00:10:58.510 --> 00:11:00.970
It's food that luckily washed up here.

183
00:11:00.970 --> 00:11:04.390
With the portions you're used to,
it'll only last you five days.

184
00:11:04.810 --> 00:11:06.770
Use your head and ration your food.

185
00:11:06.770 --> 00:11:09.150
It's a good thing we're both cooks.

186
00:11:13.280 --> 00:11:14.400
Wait a second!

187
00:11:14.400 --> 00:11:16.450
Is that your share?!

188
00:11:16.450 --> 00:11:19.410
It's at least three times
bigger than mine!

189
00:11:20.740 --> 00:11:23.040
Of course it is.

190
00:11:23.040 --> 00:11:24.750
I'm an adult.

191
00:11:24.750 --> 00:11:27.750
My stomach is larger than yours.

192
00:11:27.750 --> 00:11:31.000
Be grateful I'm even
sharing the food with you.

193
00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:34.970
Don't expect any pity from me.

194
00:11:37.640 --> 00:11:39.470
You old fart!

195
00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:46.480
You watch the other side of the sea.

196
00:11:46.480 --> 00:11:48.650
Let me know as soon
as you see a ship.

197
00:11:49.310 --> 00:11:54.740
Until then, no contact.
It's a waste of energy.

198
00:11:54.740 --> 00:11:56.450
Good luck.

199
00:11:57.030 --> 00:11:58.700
That old fart!

200
00:11:58.700 --> 00:12:01.160
I won't talk to him even if I see a ship.

201
00:12:01.160 --> 00:12:02.490
It'll be fine.

202
00:12:02.490 --> 00:12:04.700
I have five days worth of food.

203
00:12:04.700 --> 00:12:08.620
That's definitely enough time
for a ship or two to pass by.

204
00:12:09.250 --> 00:12:12.130
But just in case...

205
00:12:12.130 --> 00:12:14.630
I'll make it last twenty days.

206
00:12:14.630 --> 00:12:17.590
That has to be enough time
to see a passing ship.

207
00:12:18.340 --> 00:12:21.050
It'll be all right. I'll definitely survive.

208
00:12:21.050 --> 00:12:22.300
It's easy!

209
00:12:35.860 --> 00:12:37.610
No ship passed by today.

210
00:12:38.780 --> 00:12:42.070
No problem. I'll just be
patient for a few more days.

211
00:12:48.370 --> 00:12:50.420
I don't wanna die...

212
00:13:01.840 --> 00:13:03.510
My last loaf of bread.

213
00:13:03.970 --> 00:13:05.390
It's kind of moldy...

214
00:13:13.230 --> 00:13:18.490
What a waste to leave
so much food...

215
00:13:19.030 --> 00:13:22.070
You need to stop eating
the customers' leftovers.

216
00:13:22.070 --> 00:13:25.200
Some of the food I threw out
earlier looked gross.

217
00:13:25.580 --> 00:13:27.910
Why don't you have some, too, huh?

218
00:13:28.500 --> 00:13:31.870
I don't want it!

219
00:13:53.150 --> 00:13:55.360
My last loaf of bread...!

220
00:14:31.890 --> 00:14:34.100
I wonder if that old fart...

221
00:14:34.100 --> 00:14:36.060
kicked the bucket yet...

222
00:14:44.280 --> 00:14:46.070
He's still alive...?

223
00:14:46.780 --> 00:14:48.910
And look at all his food!

224
00:14:49.740 --> 00:14:51.370
He still has so much!

225
00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:55.830
There's that much food!

226
00:14:59.840 --> 00:15:02.840
I'll take it no matter what.

227
00:15:02.840 --> 00:15:05.970
It was all his fault to begin with!

228
00:15:06.640 --> 00:15:08.800
I want to live!

229
00:15:16.270 --> 00:15:18.770
What are you doing
over here, little eggplant?

230
00:15:21.780 --> 00:15:23.940
Did you see a ship or something?

231
00:15:27.820 --> 00:15:30.700
I came to steal your food.

232
00:15:30.700 --> 00:15:32.950
If you think you can kill me, go ahead.

233
00:15:32.950 --> 00:15:35.910
I'll die of starvation anyway.

234
00:15:38.500 --> 00:15:39.920
All this food to yourself...!

235
00:15:57.390 --> 00:16:01.980
Weren't we going to stay out of contact
with each other until we saw a ship?

236
00:16:03.480 --> 00:16:04.820
Why?

237
00:16:06.070 --> 00:16:07.820
This is all treasure...

238
00:16:08.240 --> 00:16:12.160
Isn't it odd that we can't eat
despite having so much money?

239
00:16:14.080 --> 00:16:14.910
Hey...

240
00:16:15.580 --> 00:16:18.540
This bag is filled with treasure...

241
00:16:25.090 --> 00:16:26.010
What the hell?!

242
00:16:26.010 --> 00:16:28.130
What's going on here?!

243
00:16:28.130 --> 00:16:29.640
Where's your food?

244
00:16:29.640 --> 00:16:32.140
You haven't eaten this whole time?!

245
00:16:32.140 --> 00:16:34.720
Hey! Say something!

246
00:16:45.650 --> 00:16:47.950
What happened to your leg?

247
00:16:49.240 --> 00:16:52.820
And what about the food?
Did you give it all to me?!

248
00:16:54.700 --> 00:16:55.830
That's right.

249
00:16:56.290 --> 00:17:00.710
Without your leg, doesn't that mean
your days as a pirate are over?!

250
00:17:00.710 --> 00:17:02.170
That goes without saying.

251
00:17:03.090 --> 00:17:04.670
Why, though?!

252
00:17:04.670 --> 00:17:06.420
I never asked for your help!

253
00:17:06.420 --> 00:17:09.760
There's no reason for you
to be kind to me!

254
00:17:11.430 --> 00:17:12.550
So why...?

255
00:17:13.260 --> 00:17:14.350
Why'd you do it?!

256
00:17:14.350 --> 00:17:15.720
Because you...

257
00:17:16.680 --> 00:17:20.770
Because you and I share a dream.

258
00:17:22.520 --> 00:17:23.770
The All Blue...

259
00:17:25.480 --> 00:17:26.190
But...

260
00:17:26.820 --> 00:17:29.190
even your men said it doesn't exist.

261
00:17:29.190 --> 00:17:31.110
But it does!

262
00:17:31.110 --> 00:17:34.240
When the time comes,
head to the Grand Line.

263
00:17:34.240 --> 00:17:37.200
You'll surely find the All Blue there.

264
00:17:37.700 --> 00:17:41.330
As you pointed out,
my pirating days are over,

265
00:17:41.330 --> 00:17:44.250
so that's why it'll be you
who goes and finds it.

266
00:17:46.420 --> 00:17:48.670
H-Hey! Geezer, don't die!

267
00:17:48.670 --> 00:17:52.800
Don't you be selfish and die on me!

268
00:17:53.550 --> 00:17:56.100
I-I wonder...

269
00:17:57.390 --> 00:18:01.770
I wonder how many people
have died cursing the sea...

270
00:18:01.770 --> 00:18:03.730
and its grandness...

271
00:18:05.360 --> 00:18:09.780
I've experienced crises like this
where I was starving.

272
00:18:09.780 --> 00:18:11.700
And each time, I wished...

273
00:18:12.490 --> 00:18:16.780
that there was a restaurant
in the middle of the sea.

274
00:18:16.780 --> 00:18:17.660
A restaurant?

275
00:18:17.660 --> 00:18:21.160
Yeah. I was thinking that
if I could leave this place alive,

276
00:18:21.160 --> 00:18:26.210
I'd build a restaurant and dedicate
the rest of my life to it.

277
00:18:26.210 --> 00:18:28.710
Alright! I'll help you do just that!

278
00:18:28.710 --> 00:18:30.300
So don't die!

279
00:18:31.670 --> 00:18:34.800
A weak little eggplant like you
couldn't possibly help!

280
00:18:34.800 --> 00:18:36.640
Then I'll get stronger!

281
00:18:37.640 --> 00:18:40.600
So... don't die!

282
00:18:51.320 --> 00:18:53.570
Hey!

283
00:18:54.240 --> 00:18:56.110
Help!

284
00:18:56.700 --> 00:18:58.330
You gotta help him!

285
00:18:58.330 --> 00:19:01.500
Please help the old fart!

286
00:19:04.460 --> 00:19:06.540
Hey!

287
00:19:07.380 --> 00:19:17.890
Hey!

288
00:19:20.310 --> 00:19:22.350
The old fart...

289
00:19:22.930 --> 00:19:26.850
gave up his leg so that I could live.

290
00:19:26.850 --> 00:19:28.480
– What?!
– What?!

291
00:19:30.570 --> 00:19:31.980
I can't...

292
00:19:32.820 --> 00:19:37.910
I can't repay the old fart for his kindness
unless I risk my life for him, too!

293
00:19:43.700 --> 00:19:47.920
Why are you getting up... Sanji?!

294
00:19:49.790 --> 00:19:53.760
I'm getting up to keep this place
a restaurant for just a moment longer.

295
00:19:55.220 --> 00:19:57.720
Does that asshole have a death wish?!

296
00:20:01.050 --> 00:20:03.390
Damn brat...!

297
00:20:04.020 --> 00:20:07.140
You put it so elegantly for us.

298
00:20:07.140 --> 00:20:09.900
But this restaurant is closing shop,

299
00:20:10.560 --> 00:20:13.650
and it will henceforth be a pirate ship!

300
00:20:16.280 --> 00:20:17.530
Stop it, you idiot!

301
00:20:17.530 --> 00:20:19.160
Keep your hands off of them!

302
00:20:20.120 --> 00:20:21.620
What's he about to do?

303
00:20:23.950 --> 00:20:27.500
Gum-Gum...

304
00:20:27.500 --> 00:20:29.250
Battle Axe!

305
00:20:35.340 --> 00:20:42.200
As a kid, I had a dream of a dazzling treasure

306
00:20:42.400 --> 00:20:49.220
I had a map in my head that I knew would lead me

307
00:20:49.470 --> 00:20:56.320
Charted a course all on my own, so nobody would beat me

308
00:20:56.440 --> 00:21:03.580
The promised land was in my hand, drew a line in the sand

309
00:21:06.280 --> 00:21:08.960
Look where I am

310
00:21:11.190 --> 00:21:17.370
My one ambition's slipping right through my hands

311
00:21:17.710 --> 00:21:24.640
But if the world ever changes I'll call out your name

312
00:21:24.800 --> 00:21:31.720
We could return to a time when our lives were still the same

313
00:21:31.850 --> 00:21:38.850
Take me to the place where memories remain

314
00:21:38.950 --> 00:21:44.720
Please don't ever let them fade
